cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.SD, cs.SOC, cs.CR 

This paper examines the geospatial characteristics of a social movement communication network, which involves the analysis of large-scale data and network structures. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Additionally, the paper also discusses the use of networked communication technologies, which could fall under cs.CY (Computers and Society) and cs.SD (Software Engineering). The paper also touches upon social movement theory, which could be categorized under cs.SOC (Social and Information Networks) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
